there were five people in the theatre and three of them were old ladies who talked so loudly throughout the whole movie and i went back and forth between being annoyed but also really invested in their conversation about how thick brick walls actually are, dining rooms, and their friend who was on vacation in pennsylvania. i didn’t like when they said “oh, blacks moved in” and complained every time we cut to the native americans. they really seemed to shift between ragging on this movie deservedly but also like they loved tom hanks but then were always vocally confused when we jumped through time. bad experience but, to be fair, it was a bad movie. the other two people in the theatre kept shushing and eventually yelled at them but i think they were hard of hearing and nothing happened. the CGI de-aging didn’t scare me too much but i really didn’t like the face morph transitions.
